I'm not the normal uncle or whatever.

39:24.917 --> 39:28.625
But I just wanted you
to know that I love you very much.

39:28.625 --> 39:31.250
And I'm really happy
to be with you on Christmas.

39:32.333 --> 39:33.458
And I, you know, I just wish

39:33.458 --> 39:35.958
everything could go back
to the way it used to be, you know?

39:36.625 --> 39:39.458
- I don't think
that's possible, Uncle Kris.

39:39.458 --> 39:41.792
- No, no, no. It is!
It is. I'm telling you!

39:41.792 --> 39:45.208
You know, everything's gonna
be totally normal from here on out.

39:45.208 --> 39:47.875
[doorbell rings]
Fuck! That's the cops. It's the cops.

39:47.875 --> 39:49.958
Okay. You haven't seen me.
You haven't seen me at all--

39:49.958 --> 39:53.167
Oh, no. You've seen me,
but I was far away. Just say that.

39:54.750 --> 39:55.750
- Okay.

39:57.125 --> 40:00.125
- That motherfucker
is cheating on me! I know it!

40:00.125 --> 40:02.625
- Who, Hags? No. [scoffs]
- Obviously!

40:02.625 --> 40:06.375
- He wouldn't cheat on you.
He is so, so, so scared of you, and--

40:06.375 --> 40:09.542
- Kimmi, is that your weird uncle
hiding behind the Christmas tree?

40:09.542 --> 40:11.458
- Oh, hey! Yeah.

40:11.458 --> 40:13.625
Merry Christmas.
You look good, look festive.

40:13.625 --> 40:15.833
You seem happy. How's your dad?

40:15.833 --> 40:18.542
- Uh, you know, staying out of jail.

40:18.542 --> 40:21.125
- No way! It's hard to do.
Trust me. [chuckles]

40:21.125 --> 40:23.917
So anyway, I'm gonna go
put some stuff on the sleigh.

40:23.917 --> 40:25.667
Christmas is right around the corner!

40:26.333 --> 40:30.333
Uh, anyway, you guys go back
to your girl problem. [laughs]

40:30.917 --> 40:33.292
Let me just say
from the bottom of my heart, Sarah,

40:33.292 --> 40:35.833
I'm so glad you're not the DEA. Seriously.

40:35.833 --> 40:37.208
- Right. Me too.
- Yeah.

40:37.833 --> 40:39.292
UNCLE KRIS:
Ho-ho-ho-ho!

40:40.250 --> 40:42.917
- Yeah, he used to dress like Santa
every Christmas,

40:42.917 --> 40:45.917
but somewhere down the road,
it became full-time.

40:45.917 --> 40:47.708
SARAH:
Some people are so crazy.

40:47.708 --> 40:50.750
Anyway, I have a tracker
on Hags' phone and iPad.

40:50.750 --> 40:53.708
I pinged all the cell towers
at every location he's been to today,

40:53.708 --> 40:55.708
cross-referenced it
with the location of his laptop,

40:55.708 --> 40:56.750
which I also have bugged,

40:56.750 --> 40:59.333
so triangulation
should be fairly straightforward.

40:59.833 --> 41:01.542
We need to follow him
and see where he's going.

41:01.542 --> 41:03.833
KIMMI:
Yeah, that's totally normal and healthy

41:03.833 --> 41:06.375
and not at all psychotic,
but, um, I can't.

41:06.375 --> 41:08.625
Uh, I have to be
at Winter Wonderland at 09:00,

41:08.625 --> 41:11.042
and I still need to find
this stupid fucking Christmas Owl.

41:11.042 --> 41:12.208
Otherwise, my mom--
- Oh, my God!

41:12.208 --> 41:14.083
There has to be something in here
that'll loosen you up.

41:14.083 --> 41:16.500
- I don't need to be loosened!
I'm not binging!

41:16.500 --> 41:19.750
We actually are
a very upstanding family, okay?

41:19.750 --> 41:25.375
- Okay! Ladies, ladies.
Hey, everything's totally fine.

41:25.375 --> 41:27.708
You know what?
It's more than fine. Merry Christmas!

41:27.708 --> 41:31.125
It's just-- The neighbors, I think,
recognized me and called the cops

41:31.125 --> 41:32.750
while I was decorating my sleigh.

41:32.750 --> 41:34.208
- The squad car he stole.

41:34.208 --> 41:35.083
- Right.

41:35.083 --> 41:36.708
- Look, again, everything's totally fine.

41:36.708 --> 41:39.458
We just probably wanna leave
within the next two or three minutes,

41:39.458 --> 41:42.583
or there's gonna be
a lot of angry banter over a megaphone

41:42.583 --> 41:45.917
and, uh, I dunno, possible gunfire.
Maybe. I don't know.

41:45.917 --> 41:47.250
- Somebody kill me.

41:49.000 --> 41:50.333
HAGS: Andrew?
ANDREW: [over phone] Hello?

41:50.333 --> 41:52.333
- Andrew, hey! Hey, okay, listen.

41:52.333 --> 41:54.708
I'm outside of the old high school,
and it's fucking freezing out here.

41:54.708 --> 41:55.458
Where are you?

41:55.458 --> 41:57.750
ANDREW: [over phone]
Just kidding. This is a voice mail. Beep.

41:57.750 --> 41:58.792
- Damn!

41:58.792 --> 42:00.500
ANDREW: [over phone]
Just kidding. I'm still here. Go on.

42:00.500 --> 42:01.708
- Oh, shit. Okay, cool.

42:01.708 --> 42:04.250
Listen, I-- I lost
Sarah's grandma's ring that was like--

42:04.250 --> 42:05.083
ANDREW: [over phone] Uh-huh.

42:05.083 --> 42:06.625
- I was in a hot tub with her dad.
ANDREW: [over phone] Yeah?

42:06.625 --> 42:07.792
- It's crazy. Can you come pick me up?

42:07.792 --> 42:08.792
ANDREW: [over phone]
That's so interesting.

42:08.792 --> 42:10.333
I'd love to hear more about this story.

42:10.333 --> 42:12.208
- Yeah, okay,
so I texted somebody for a ride,

42:12.208 --> 42:13.333
but they haven't gotten back to me yet.

42:13.333 --> 42:15.292
And-- And I'm-- I'm out here in the cold.
ANDREW: [over phone] Yeah?

42:15.292 --> 42:16.417
- The ring's in the orphanage.
ANDREW: [over phone] Uh-huh.

42:16.417 --> 42:19.208
- I just need somebody to come get me
'cause I'm high on cocaine.

42:19.208 --> 42:21.833
I'm warm on my inside
and cold in my toes and fingers!

42:21.833 --> 42:23.667
ANDREW: [over phone] That's crazy.
- So please, can you come get me?

42:23.667 --> 42:25.792
ANDREW: [over phone]
Only thing is I'm not here. [laughs]

42:25.792 --> 42:26.667
[voice mail beeps]

42:26.667 --> 42:28.750
- Oh, you-- you sick,
twisted motherfucker, man!

42:28.750 --> 42:30.292
I told you to stop doing this shit!

42:30.292 --> 42:33.250
[vehicle approaching]
Hey, hey! Right here!

42:34.208 --> 42:35.583
Right here!

42:35.583 --> 42:36.792
[car stops]

42:37.500 --> 42:38.750
Thank God.

42:38.750 --> 42:41.208
Okay, if I pull this off,

42:41.208 --> 42:43.583
I promise, we ain't got
no more problems, okay?

42:43.583 --> 42:46.000
You and me, forever. Just-- Thank you.

42:46.000 --> 42:46.875
Hey!

42:49.250 --> 42:50.375
[knocks on window]

42:51.958 --> 42:55.000
♪ Pimp my ride ♪

42:55.708 --> 42:56.708
- Hey.

42:56.708 --> 42:59.542
Did somebody say Pimp My Ride
three times in the mirror?

42:59.542 --> 43:01.000
[laughs]
HAGS: Pompano Mike!

43:01.000 --> 43:02.750
First of all, Merry Christmas.
POMPANO MIKE: Same.

43:02.750 --> 43:05.625
- Second of all,
is there any way you can gimme a ride?

43:05.625 --> 43:07.417
- Let's make some donuts, motherfucker.
Get in!

43:07.417 --> 43:08.292
- Okay!
POMPANO MIKE: Okay!

43:08.292 --> 43:10.583
♪ Pimp my ride ♪

43:12.500 --> 43:15.208
- All right. To the orphanage we go.

43:15.208 --> 43:17.083
- I didn't know
there was gonna be another person in here.

43:17.083 --> 43:22.542
- Not just a person,
a force of friggin' nature.

43:22.542 --> 43:26.000
- Ooo-kay. I'm Delray Donna.
- I'm Hags.

43:26.000 --> 43:29.333
- I'm-- Pompano over here--
his life partner and spiritual advisor.

43:29.333 --> 43:30.167
- Yeah.

43:30.167 --> 43:31.458
- Are you from Delray?

43:31.458 --> 43:36.000
- [laughs] No, no, no!
No, no way, dude!

43:36.000 --> 43:38.292
I'm just living
in that south Florida state of mind.

43:38.292 --> 43:39.875
- That's right, baby.
HAGS: Should've known.

43:39.875 --> 43:42.917
- Hey, it is so darn good to see you!
- Good to see you.

43:42.917 --> 43:45.708
- What's going on? What's new?
You still training for the Olympics?

43:45.708 --> 43:47.875
- I heard you do long put.
- No!

43:47.875 --> 43:49.000
- Long jumps?

43:49.000 --> 43:51.125
- Never did an Olympic thing in my life.
- No?

43:51.125 --> 43:54.042
- But I am about to make
the biggest decision of my life.

43:54.042 --> 43:56.625
- Ooh.
- Oh. Whether or not
to start training for the Olympics?

43:56.625 --> 43:57.667
- Ooh.

43:57.667 --> 44:00.750
- No. I'm proposing
to my girlfriend, Sarah.

44:00.750 --> 44:02.167
- Oh, my God!
- Ah.

44:02.167 --> 44:04.167
POMPANO MIKE: That is awesome!
- That is beautiful.

44:04.167 --> 44:07.000
- Can I get a little peek of that ring?
- I'd love to see that charmer.

44:07.000 --> 44:10.375
- I accidentally donated the ring
to the orphanage, so.

44:10.375 --> 44:12.417
- Oh, tale as old as time.
- I gotta go get it.

44:12.417 --> 44:14.542
DELRAY DONNA: Darn.
- Oh, no!

44:14.542 --> 44:15.958
- Can you keep your eyes on the road?

44:15.958 --> 44:17.417
[Delray Donna and Pompano Mike laughing]

44:17.417 --> 44:19.500
- Where we're going, there are no roads.

44:19.500 --> 44:22.208
- When you live in your car,
you don't work a day in your life.

44:22.208 --> 44:23.667
POMPANO MIKE:
Oh, amen.

44:23.667 --> 44:25.958
Baby, we're being rude and also impolite.

44:25.958 --> 44:29.583
It's Hanukkah here in Binge Town,
and we should give him a Mazel-Tug.

44:29.583 --> 44:30.583
- Oh, wow!
POMPANO MIKE: Yes.

44:30.583 --> 44:31.833
- Here you go. Choo-choo, baby.

44:31.833 --> 44:35.208
- Here's to merriment,
here's to friendship,

44:35.208 --> 44:36.500
to proposals,

44:36.500 --> 44:39.750
and most of all, suck it down pipe!

44:39.750 --> 44:41.917
- Suck it down pipe.
HAGS: No, thank you, guys.

44:41.917 --> 44:44.167
I appreciate it, though.
- Yeah, ooh, we understand.

44:44.167 --> 44:45.292
- We're on the same wavelength.

44:45.292 --> 44:46.958
- Totally get it. We get it.
- Thank you.

44:46.958 --> 44:49.042
- Pipe, suck it, down it.

44:49.042 --> 44:50.833
- Take the pipe. Suck it down.

44:50.833 --> 44:52.583
- Suck-a that pipe suck stick, Piper.

44:52.583 --> 44:55.083
- ♪ Suck be a piper tonight ♪

44:55.083 --> 44:56.958
- ♪ Waiting for some pipe ♪

44:56.958 --> 45:00.667
- Everybody says the secret to suck-cess
is-- is opening yourself to all the...

45:00.667 --> 45:01.792
DELRAY DONNA AND POMPANO MIKE:
Pipeabilities.

45:01.792 --> 45:02.917
- Okay. Can you stop?

45:02.917 --> 45:04.583
DELRAY DONNA AND POMPANO MIKE:
♪ How much pipe could a pipe suck suck ♪

45:04.583 --> 45:06.125
♪ If a pipe suck could suck pipe ♪

45:06.125 --> 45:09.167
- Okay, okay. If I smoke it,
will you please stop making puns?

45:09.167 --> 45:10.167
I'm begging you.

45:13.417 --> 45:14.667
DELRAY DONNA AND POMPANO MIKE:
Maybe.

45:15.417 --> 45:17.542
- Okay.
- All right!

45:17.542 --> 45:19.625
- All right! There he goes.
POMPANO MIKE: Yeah.

45:19.625 --> 45:21.833
- That's the beautiful power
of peer pressure.

45:21.833 --> 45:24.375
- Hey, have you ever seen
the feature film length feature

45:24.375 --> 45:25.792
Honey, I Sucked the Pipe?

45:27.125 --> 45:28.417
- So this is what again?

45:28.417 --> 45:29.750
- That one's got a little Crunch in it.

45:30.625 --> 45:31.750
- What's Crunch?

45:31.750 --> 45:33.583
- Yeah. Little Corgi's Gone Wild.

45:33.583 --> 45:35.458
- This one's Medulla All-Blunt-Gatta.

45:35.458 --> 45:37.083
Christopher Mintz Plasse.

45:37.083 --> 45:37.917
- Greek Lettuce.

45:37.917 --> 45:39.500
- The bassist from Smash Mouth.

45:39.500 --> 45:40.542
- That one's the Three Wood.

45:40.542 --> 45:41.333
- Sneeze!

45:41.333 --> 45:44.417
- The tiny thing they put in a pizza box
to keep it from flattening.

45:44.417 --> 45:45.583
- You got a little bit
of Baby Gerkin there.

45:45.583 --> 45:48.708
POMPANO MIKE:
Greenpeace, Cub Scout,
Yellow Belly, Wet Willy, Circuit City.

45:48.708 --> 45:51.333
- Guys, I'm smoking it!
Can you just stop speaking?

45:51.333 --> 45:54.417
- Well, you better crank that suck pipe
'cause we're already at the orphanage.

45:54.417 --> 45:55.708
DELRAY DONNA: Ooh.
[Hags coughing]

45:55.708 --> 45:57.792
POMPANO MIKE: Oh, did I say
that last one was Circuit City?

45:57.792 --> 45:59.958
I actually think it's Mambo Number 6.

45:59.958 --> 46:03.000
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

46:05.958 --> 46:07.417
ANDREW:
What the fuck is this?

46:07.417 --> 46:09.250
I would never put up these decorations.

46:09.250 --> 46:13.542
- Andy, you don't exist in this universe.

46:13.542 --> 46:14.667
Do you understand?

46:14.667 --> 46:17.917
This is what it would be like
if you were never born.

46:17.917 --> 46:19.250
- Oh.
- Come on.

46:19.750 --> 46:23.292
- ♪ My present to you ♪
[all clapping]

46:23.292 --> 46:27.458
- Oh, golly, Mother. This is fantastic!

46:27.458 --> 46:30.958
[continues singing]

46:30.958 --> 46:32.000
[laughing]

46:32.000 --> 46:33.542
- You've certainly outdone yourself.

46:34.833 --> 46:37.208
- Before we eat, I'd like to say grace.

46:37.208 --> 46:38.792
- Yes!
- Grace.

46:38.792 --> 46:39.792
- Here we go.

46:40.458 --> 46:44.208
DEIDRE: Dear heavenly Lord,
we thank you for this delicious meal

46:44.208 --> 46:46.667
and for all of the beautiful blessings
that surround us.

46:47.417 --> 46:50.917
This is a time
of self-reflection and redemption.

46:50.917 --> 46:55.125
All of our past misdeeds
can be undone with love,

46:55.750 --> 46:59.042
and, of course, the perfect family.
[Rigo mouthing "Family"]

46:59.042 --> 47:00.417
- Amen. [laughs]
- Amen.

47:00.417 --> 47:01.750
- This is terrifying.

47:01.750 --> 47:05.250
- When you have a perfect son,
there is no need to make another.

47:05.250 --> 47:07.792
- Oh, I'm so glad
it was only the three of us growing up.

47:07.792 --> 47:09.458
- I know!

47:09.458 --> 47:13.125
[clinks on glass]
- I was going to wait till Christmas
morning to tell you guys.

47:13.125 --> 47:17.458
I brilliantly decided
to invest in Titcoin.

47:17.458 --> 47:19.458
- Oh, how exotic!

47:19.458 --> 47:22.667
- And it paid out big, real big.

47:22.667 --> 47:25.167
$40 million!

47:25.167 --> 47:26.792
DAKOTA:
Rigo!

47:26.792 --> 47:29.708
- [laughs] What do you guys want?
Do you want the moon?

47:29.708 --> 47:32.542
Just say it,
and I'll buy it for you with Titcoin!

47:32.542 --> 47:36.583
- This is truly
the merriest Christmas of all.

47:36.583 --> 47:38.250
- My work here is done.

47:38.250 --> 47:39.875
- Wha-- What are you talking about
your work here is done?

47:39.875 --> 47:41.000
You haven't done anything for me!

47:41.000 --> 47:43.292
- It's a Christmas miracle! Look it.

47:43.917 --> 47:45.542
Family. Happy. Joyous.

47:45.958 --> 47:48.250
I left my house when I was seven,

47:48.250 --> 47:53.750
and the only thing I miss
is my mother's golden brown chicken wings.

47:53.750 --> 47:57.125
Boy, and your mother
must be one hell of a cook.

47:57.125 --> 47:58.208
- No, no, she isn't.

47:58.208 --> 48:00.167
In fact, she burns everything she touches.

48:00.167 --> 48:02.958
And, hey, isn't this supposed
to be going the other way around, man?

48:02.958 --> 48:06.333
Isn't the whole point of this fantasy
to prove that things are much worse

48:06.333 --> 48:08.917
with me not around?
[Angel snoring]

48:08.917 --> 48:10.708
ANDREW:
Angel. Angel?

48:11.208 --> 48:12.208
Angel?

48:12.208 --> 48:13.917
- Hey, who the fuck are you?

48:13.917 --> 48:16.542
- I-- I'm Andrew.
I met you under the bridge.

48:16.542 --> 48:18.583
- Under the bridge?
That don't sound like me, homes.

48:18.583 --> 48:19.792
- You took me to your tent, man!

48:19.792 --> 48:21.417
You said it was in your family
for generations!

48:22.083 --> 48:23.625
- Oh, wait. I remember, yeah!

48:23.625 --> 48:25.750
Chicken wings. My mother's chicken wings--

48:25.750 --> 48:27.708
- No, no, no. You already told me that.
You told me that already.

48:27.708 --> 48:28.833
- Did I fix your life?

48:28.833 --> 48:29.833
- No, not at all.

48:29.833 --> 48:32.250
RIGO: Eskimo kisses!
[Deidre squealing]

48:32.250 --> 48:34.458
- Oh, my God, this isn't right.
I can't look at this.

48:34.458 --> 48:37.167
- You gotta lose your attitude, homes.
It sucks!

48:37.917 --> 48:39.167
All right, here we go.

48:40.125 --> 48:42.708
NEWS ANCHOR:
Winter Wonderland
has just opened its doors.

48:42.708 --> 48:44.875
And I have to say,
the mood here is slightly strange

48:44.875 --> 48:48.042
as The Binge has brought in
a different class of people.

48:48.042 --> 48:49.833
Uh, sir, what brings you
to Winter Wonderland?

48:49.833 --> 48:53.708
- Hey, we came here to party
and eat some fucking ass, yo!

48:53.708 --> 48:55.333
[group cheering]

48:55.333 --> 48:57.125
- Now, when you say eat ass,

48:57.125 --> 49:00.583
uh, is that metaphorically, or are you
actually going to perform a sex act?

49:01.750 --> 49:05.958
- I, metaphorically, am gonna eat
some fucking ass, literally, dude!

49:05.958 --> 49:08.000
[group cheering]

49:08.000 --> 49:09.875
- While confusing,
I think I get your point.

49:09.875 --> 49:12.042
So inside, there are families gathering,

49:12.042 --> 49:13.708
children are having a great time.

49:13.708 --> 49:16.083
Now, sir, it seems like you have
a group of friends here.

49:16.083 --> 49:17.000
Are you expecting anymore?

49:17.500 --> 49:18.500
- Oh, hell yeah.

49:18.500 --> 49:19.750
The Bingers are coming, man.

49:19.750 --> 49:21.750
We're taking over, all right?
- Okay.

49:21.750 --> 49:24.583
- We are gonna turn Winter Wonderland

49:24.583 --> 49:26.083
into Binger...

49:27.292 --> 49:29.083
Fingerland, dude!

49:29.083 --> 49:30.333
[group laughing, cheering]

49:30.333 --> 49:34.667
- But, uh, while I don't agree that
that pun was as strong as it could be,

49:34.667 --> 49:36.000
I do agree with the sentiment.

49:36.000 --> 49:38.500
Uh, the Bingers are coming.

49:38.500 --> 49:40.458
[group cheering]

49:40.458 --> 49:42.625
♪ "We Wish You a Merry Christmas"
playing ♪

49:45.667 --> 49:48.000
- Enjoy. Vote for Mayor Spengler.

49:48.792 --> 49:50.583
- I'm allergic to nuts.

49:50.583 --> 49:53.042
- Well, what did you think was going
to happen at the nutcracker station?

49:53.042 --> 49:54.917
I have a secret for you, okay?

49:54.917 --> 49:57.917
Complaining makes Santa very, very angry.

49:58.417 --> 49:59.542
But I'm okay with it.

49:59.542 --> 50:02.458
[laughs] There you go. Merry Christmas!

50:02.458 --> 50:04.958
- Life's short. You gotta make sure
you live it, all right?

50:04.958 --> 50:07.417
Eleven months out of the year,
I'm at a Scion dealership.

50:07.417 --> 50:09.417
Yeah, I, uh, see, you think this is...

50:09.417 --> 50:10.417
It's hot under here.

50:11.625 --> 50:13.250
One sec. Don't ever do this.

50:13.250 --> 50:15.333
Now everybody has
a friggin' podcast nowadays.

50:15.333 --> 50:18.417
How long can you talk about presents
and good kids and stuff like that?

50:18.417 --> 50:20.333
Are you good? You look like my first wife.

50:20.333 --> 50:21.958
You're just staring through my brain.

50:21.958 --> 50:23.542
- Excuse me, sweet angel!

50:23.542 --> 50:26.958
Hey! There is no binging
when you're Santa Claus!

50:26.958 --> 50:29.167
- [laughs] Looks like there is.

50:29.167 --> 50:30.333
- Out! Get outta here!

50:30.333 --> 50:31.667
Just get out. Get outta here right now.

50:31.667 --> 50:33.750
- [burps] Wait. You want me to leave?

50:34.542 --> 50:37.042
- Well, this ain't Trivial Pursuit,

50:37.042 --> 50:39.000
so I wouldn't take the Risk.

50:39.500 --> 50:40.583
- Hmm?
- Mm.

50:41.750 --> 50:42.750
- What?

50:43.292 --> 50:44.750
- Like the board games!

50:44.750 --> 50:47.458
- I know what you mean,
but why would you say that to me?

50:47.458 --> 50:49.458
[kids laughing]

50:50.250 --> 50:51.542
- I don't even know where you get a gun.

50:51.542 --> 50:53.458
- Get the fuck outta here! Go!

50:53.458 --> 50:54.708
- All right.

50:54.708 --> 50:56.333
MAYOR SPENGLER: Search that bag!
GUARD: All right.

50:56.333 --> 50:57.417
- My phone, Larry!

50:57.417 --> 50:58.750
God damn it, Santa!

50:58.750 --> 51:00.042
SANTA:
Here, little girl. You can have my bell.

51:00.458 --> 51:03.083
MAYOR SPENGLER:
Hi. Could you eat your ice cream
while you're not staring at me?

51:03.083 --> 51:04.958
Thank you so much! Merry Christmas!

51:04.958 --> 51:06.958
Hey, Four Eyes! Take your glasses off!

51:06.958 --> 51:08.292
Okay, now there's nothing to see.

51:08.292 --> 51:09.458
G-G-G-Go!

51:09.458 --> 51:11.333
UNCLE KRIS:
Okay! Nobody panic.

51:11.333 --> 51:12.958
He probably just
pulled over the wrong car.

51:12.958 --> 51:14.292
SARAH:
Uh, yeah, I doubt that,

51:14.292 --> 51:17.667
considering you're in a stolen cop car
with a reindeer stashed on the roof.

51:17.667 --> 51:18.667
[phone ringing]
- Everybody, shut up!

51:18.667 --> 51:20.000
Shut up! My mom's calling.

51:20.000 --> 51:21.667
- Oh, tell her I said hi.
- I will not!

51:22.583 --> 51:24.833
- Heyyy.
MAYOR SPENGLER: [over phone]
Kimberly, where are you?

51:24.833 --> 51:27.125
KIMMI: [over phone]
Uh, we're-- we're at church.

51:27.125 --> 51:28.458
[sirens wailing]
- What are those sirens?

51:29.125 --> 51:30.667
- Church sirens.

51:30.667 --> 51:32.792
MAYOR SPENGLER: [over phone]
Church sirens are not a thing!

51:32.792 --> 51:34.583
- Hags is at the orphanage.
We need to go to the orphanage.

51:34.583 --> 51:35.750
Step on it, Santa!

51:35.750 --> 51:39.500
- No, no, no. We gotta be super chill,
and then maybe he'll just go away.

51:39.500 --> 51:40.750
OFFICER: [over speaker]
Keep your hands where I can see them.

51:40.750 --> 51:41.750
[Uncle Kris gasps]

51:41.750 --> 51:43.125
- Oh!
MAYOR SPENGLER: [over phone] Who's that?

51:43.750 --> 51:45.083
- That's a song!

51:45.083 --> 51:46.250
Uh-- Uh--

51:46.250 --> 51:49.417
♪ Keep your hands up for Christmas, baby ♪

51:49.417 --> 51:51.708
♪ Keep your hands up ♪

51:51.708 --> 51:55.042
♪ Keep your hands up for Christmas, baby ♪

51:55.042 --> 51:57.542
♪ Keep your hands up for Christmas,
baby ♪

51:57.542 --> 51:59.125
♪ Keep your hands up ♪

51:59.125 --> 52:00.250
- That's not a song!

52:00.250 --> 52:03.292
- ♪ Keep your hands up for Christmas
Keep your hands up for Christmas ♪

52:03.292 --> 52:05.667
- Where did you learn this song?
In school?

52:05.667 --> 52:06.667
Are you binging?

52:06.667 --> 52:08.250
Because it is almost 9:00 p.m.,

52:08.250 --> 52:10.125
and that owl is the cornerstone of the--

52:10.125 --> 52:11.292
- Wait, did she just say
it's nine o'clock?

52:11.292 --> 52:12.750
It's time for the exploding ketamine.

52:12.750 --> 52:13.958
- What's that?
- No, he wants to do it.

52:13.958 --> 52:14.875
MAYOR SPENGLER:
Please be honest with me

52:14.875 --> 52:16.292
because I'm at the end of my rope!

52:16.292 --> 52:18.333
- No, I'm actually
gonna see you later. Bye.

52:18.333 --> 52:20.417
- Your lack of respect Boggles the mind!

52:20.417 --> 52:21.500
[line disconnects]

52:22.667 --> 52:23.667
That was a good one.

52:23.667 --> 52:25.625
- Ladies, ladies!

52:25.625 --> 52:29.333
Everybody be super still and super quiet,

52:29.333 --> 52:31.792
and then maybe
he'll just walk right past the car.

52:31.792 --> 52:35.208
Everybody,
chain your robot that's broken.

52:35.208 --> 52:37.083
SARAH:
Why are you guys acting insane?

52:37.083 --> 52:39.167
It's legal to binge tonight.
- Don't do it, Sarah!

52:39.167 --> 52:41.083
- Don't!
UNCLE KRIS: Don't!

52:41.083 --> 52:43.375
- See, it's-- it's fine.

52:43.375 --> 52:44.583
[Kimmi exhales in relief]

52:45.583 --> 52:46.875
[box explodes]
UNCLE KRIS: Fuck!

52:46.875 --> 52:48.292
[tires screeching]

52:49.250 --> 52:50.875
[Uncle Kris speaking indistinctly]

52:50.875 --> 52:55.458
Oh-ho-ho!
It is Christmas officially! Woo!

52:55.458 --> 52:57.750
- Oh, my insides are burning!

52:57.750 --> 53:00.125
NARRATOR:
As we descend into the night,

53:00.125 --> 53:03.167
it will prove to be anything but bland.

53:03.167 --> 53:06.583
With each generation
comes a new set of lore,

53:06.583 --> 53:08.500
and we'll look to the future

53:08.500 --> 53:12.500
to learn who we really are
right at our core.

53:12.500 --> 53:15.083
- And as another Christmas comes to pass,

53:15.083 --> 53:18.542
I realize that there's
two types of people in this world,

53:18.542 --> 53:20.375
Chutes and Ladders.

53:20.375 --> 53:23.917
And this Christmas,
we're going up the ladder, baby!

53:23.917 --> 53:26.750
Yeah! Yahtzee!

53:26.750 --> 53:28.375
Ooh-hoo!
CROWD: Ooh-hoo!

53:28.375 --> 53:30.708
ANDREW:
Is that Kimmi? She became the mayor?

53:30.708 --> 53:33.292
And-- And if this is the future,
why is everything in black and white?

53:33.292 --> 53:35.542
- Hey, stop asking questions.
I'm trying to hear this.

53:35.542 --> 53:39.833
- And I'd like to thank my husband,
the single best lover of my life.

53:39.833 --> 53:41.792
Angel, come up here, baby.
- She looks so beautiful.

53:41.792 --> 53:45.542
Oh-- Whoa-oh-oh! Whoa!
[Future Angel laughing]

53:45.542 --> 53:47.625
What the hell, man? You married Kimmi?

53:47.625 --> 53:49.958
- The Lord works in mysterious ways.

53:49.958 --> 53:53.708
I am a very lucky man.
She is a wonderful woman!

53:53.708 --> 53:54.708
ANDREW: I know she is!

53:54.708 --> 53:56.667
Jesus, you're like
50 years older than her!

53:56.667 --> 53:58.708
- In the future, age doesn't matter.

53:58.708 --> 53:59.750
- What the hell does that mean?

53:59.750 --> 54:02.458
- Age is just the number of years
that you've been born!

54:02.458 --> 54:07.042
- Oh-- I mean, yeah, that--
that-- that is exactly what age means.

54:07.042 --> 54:08.750
That's-- You're correct.

54:08.750 --> 54:09.958
But, come on, man!

54:09.958 --> 54:12.542
You're supposed to be helping me,
and you married the love of my life?

54:13.042 --> 54:14.625
This is a nightmare, okay?

54:14.625 --> 54:16.208
If I ever did anything good for anybody,

54:16.208 --> 54:18.375
could you please--
could you take me there?

54:18.375 --> 54:20.167
Could you show me one scenario

54:20.167 --> 54:22.542
that was actually better off
with me in attendance?

54:22.542 --> 54:25.500
- Okay, okay. Let's go
to the Christmas dinner at your family's.

54:25.500 --> 54:27.292
- We were already there, Angel!

54:27.292 --> 54:30.292
- Are you sure?
- Yes! It was a disaster!

54:30.292 --> 54:32.375
- I don't remember, but you're the boss.

54:32.958 --> 54:35.583
But isn't there somebody special
from your past?

54:35.583 --> 54:37.792
- Yes, and you married her in the future!

54:37.792 --> 54:40.583
- Hey! Let's keep
my wonderful wife out of it, okay?

54:40.583 --> 54:43.667
You know, you are really tough to please.

54:43.667 --> 54:45.542
No wonder everybody hates you!

54:45.542 --> 54:46.708
ANDREW:
Fine. You know what?

54:46.708 --> 54:50.667
I will no longer hurt my family
or anyone else in my life, okay?

54:50.667 --> 54:54.083
How about you just take me back
to the hospital where I was born

54:54.083 --> 54:55.833
and I put myself up for adoption?

54:55.833 --> 54:58.083
That way, we erase
all of this from ever happening.

54:58.083 --> 55:01.708
That sounds like a better idea
than whatever... this is!

55:01.708 --> 55:02.708
- Your wish!

55:03.458 --> 55:04.458
MAYOR KIMMI:
Slap that tushy!

55:04.458 --> 55:06.958
- Ooh!
- Oh! Ha-ha!

55:06.958 --> 55:08.750
- We're still here--
I'm still watching this, man!

55:08.750 --> 55:11.333
- I'm not done!
[Future Angel and Kimmi laughing]

55:11.333 --> 55:13.125
DELRAY DONNA:
Hey, wake up. We're at the orphanage.

55:13.125 --> 55:14.167
- Hey.
- Hey.

55:14.750 --> 55:17.208
- I think I sucked it down two pipe.

55:17.208 --> 55:20.000
- Not possible.
- Hey. Two pipe, RIP.

55:20.000 --> 55:22.917
- So we gotta focus.
We gotta trick the shit out of this lady.

55:22.917 --> 55:25.458
- What did you say your names were?
POMPANO MIKE: I...

55:26.833 --> 55:29.250
am... Dave...

55:30.833 --> 55:31.833
id.

55:33.583 --> 55:34.708
Letterman.

55:34.708 --> 55:36.292
David-- David Letterman.

55:37.042 --> 55:38.958
- And I am...

55:42.708 --> 55:45.375
[Delray Donna mouths "Pompano Mike"]

55:45.375 --> 55:47.292
Pompano Mike.
- Yep.

55:47.292 --> 55:49.875
- Well, being fully transparent here,

55:50.958 --> 55:54.167
my first instinct is that
you're giving me fake names.

55:54.167 --> 55:57.667
[Pompano Mike gasps]
- Oh. Oh.

55:57.667 --> 56:01.625
[Hags laughs, mumbles]
- I don't know why...

56:01.625 --> 56:05.042
- Oh, that's awful.
- ...you'd accuse us of that.

56:05.042 --> 56:06.083
The audacity!

56:06.083 --> 56:10.167
- Well, the time it took you
to say your names.

56:10.167 --> 56:12.917
The looks that you gave each other
after you said each name.

56:12.917 --> 56:13.750
- Shoot.

56:13.750 --> 56:16.583
- And the names themselves
are pretty unbelievable.

56:16.583 --> 56:19.542
- Excuse me?
We would never do something like that!

56:19.542 --> 56:21.458
- Honey--
- Hey, we are very honest people.

56:21.458 --> 56:22.708
I'm sorry!
- Mike--

56:22.708 --> 56:25.583
- Okay, yeah.
See, all of this feels pretty suspect.

56:25.583 --> 56:28.542
- You are being
extremely rude and unprofessional,

56:28.542 --> 56:31.250
and I don't know why
you would accuse someone of like this.

56:31.750 --> 56:33.125
Can I have a word with you?

56:33.125 --> 56:35.958
You should be ashamed.

56:35.958 --> 56:39.042
- Okay, I did not mean to offend. I just--

56:39.042 --> 56:41.833
[laughs mockingly]

56:41.833 --> 56:45.250
- I don't know why you'd accuse us of...

56:45.250 --> 56:46.792
[mumbles indistinctly]

56:46.792 --> 56:47.792
- Extremely rude!

56:47.792 --> 56:52.042
- Oh, my God! Christmas Eve is one
of the toughest nights at the orphanage

56:52.042 --> 56:53.500
and our Santa never showed up.

56:54.333 --> 56:55.542
And these kids, they--

56:58.167 --> 56:59.375
You know what?

56:59.375 --> 57:02.292
If you wanna give me $50
to start the application process,

57:02.292 --> 57:05.250
I will give you the benefit of the doubt
and run one of your IDs.

57:05.250 --> 57:07.833
- There you go.
Oh, this is a balloon for the kids.

57:07.833 --> 57:08.750
[whispers] Put that in your butt.

57:08.750 --> 57:10.292
- I just need the ID, please.

57:10.292 --> 57:11.958
- Uh, here's the cash.
- There you go.

57:11.958 --> 57:13.958
- And your-- And your ID.

57:14.750 --> 57:16.750
GRETA: Oh, uh...
POMPANO MIKE: It's me.

57:16.750 --> 57:19.125
- I apologize, Mr. Letterman.

57:19.125 --> 57:20.292
- You're welcome.

57:20.292 --> 57:22.708
- Just one moment.
Just don't touch anything.

57:22.708 --> 57:24.458
DELRAY DONNA:
Don't you feel silly?

57:24.458 --> 57:26.667
♪ upbeat music playing ♪

57:26.667 --> 57:28.958
- [whispers] What? [laughs] Wow!

57:29.708 --> 57:33.083
That actually worked!
- Yes. Yes!

57:33.083 --> 57:35.750
- Okay, okay, shh, shh, shh.
Guys, I'm gonna get the ring.

57:35.750 --> 57:37.417
You guys go wait in the car.

57:37.417 --> 57:40.208
I'm impressed. Really impressed, guys.
That was nuts!

57:40.208 --> 57:43.167
- [whispering] Okay. See you out there.
- Wow!

57:43.167 --> 57:44.625
- Guys, guys, shh.

57:44.625 --> 57:46.167
- You got this!

57:46.167 --> 57:48.375
My God, I think she really bought it!
- I did too.

57:48.375 --> 57:49.583
- You were amazing!

57:49.583 --> 57:53.042
- You kidding me? You were incredible!

57:53.042 --> 57:55.792
I've never seen acting like that.
- Oh, yeah.

57:55.792 --> 57:57.542
- And I've watched all CBS sitcoms.

57:57.542 --> 57:59.167
- Hey, let's get outta here
before we get arrested.

57:59.167 --> 58:00.042
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

58:00.042 --> 58:02.542
- All right, everyone,
seems like Santa isn't coming this year.

58:03.125 --> 58:05.167
But we're orphans,
so it should come as no surprise

58:05.167 --> 58:08.958
that the adults around us have once again
neglected their responsibilities

58:08.958 --> 58:10.042
at our expense.

58:10.833 --> 58:13.333
But we're gonna have
an old-fashioned white elephant.

58:13.917 --> 58:15.750
You pick a number,
and that person gets to choose a present.

58:15.750 --> 58:16.958
[Grandma Ray yells]

58:16.958 --> 58:18.625
We only steal when it's our turn.

58:20.667 --> 58:21.750
- Hey.

58:22.625 --> 58:23.708
How you guys doin'?

58:23.708 --> 58:25.292
Look, I don't mean to interrupt, okay?

58:25.292 --> 58:28.042
I'm just here to get my present,
and I can be on my merry way.

58:28.042 --> 58:30.417
- You want that present?
You gotta sit down and play the game.

58:30.417 --> 58:32.333
- Okay, see,
I don't really have time to play a game

58:32.333 --> 58:33.458
'cause I'm trying to propose.

58:33.458 --> 58:38.000
So what's a little $20 say
that I can get this gift and then roll?

58:38.000 --> 58:39.583
- You think you can buy us with money?

58:39.583 --> 58:42.208
- Okay, look, here.
35 is the best I can do.

58:42.208 --> 58:44.792
See, I just got fired
and I told you, I'm trying to propose!

58:44.792 --> 58:46.333
BOY:
I don't care about your personal life!

58:46.333 --> 58:48.792
Now shut up and play.
If not, the door's right there.

58:48.792 --> 58:51.417
- Okay, watch your tone
'cause you getting mildly disrespectful!

58:51.417 --> 58:53.708
All right, I'm gonna play the game
with all of you guys.

58:53.708 --> 58:56.125
Calm your energy,
little Buddy The Elf, okay?

58:56.125 --> 58:58.167
What are we doing?
We singing Christmas carols or something?

58:58.167 --> 59:00.000
- Are you high right now?

59:00.000 --> 59:04.417
♪ "Carol of the Bells" playing ♪
[sirens wailing]

59:04.417 --> 59:06.042
[tires screeching]

59:12.667 --> 59:14.542
- You guys are real quiet back there.
Are you all right?

59:18.958 --> 59:19.958
- Mr. Letterman?

59:21.125 --> 59:22.917
[tires screeching]

59:22.917 --> 59:24.917
[sirens wailing]

59:36.917 --> 59:38.375
- It better be Santa!

59:38.375 --> 59:39.958
- We did it! Ahh!

59:40.542 --> 59:42.208
Woo! We are here!

59:42.208 --> 59:43.125
All right, come on!

59:43.125 --> 59:45.417
♪ Christmas, Christmas, woo ♪

59:45.417 --> 59:46.250
Let's go!

59:47.292 --> 59:48.583
[Uncle Kris panting]

59:49.333 --> 59:51.792
- Paul, we're paying you
to watch for bingers!

59:51.792 --> 59:53.417
- Okay, girls, let's go! Come on.

59:53.417 --> 59:56.000
- Hey, you're two hours late!

59:56.000 --> 59:58.792
That is really messed up
to do to these kids, they're orphans!

59:58.792 --> 59:59.875
I am only paying you half.

59:59.875 --> 1:00:00.708
- Where's the chimney?

1:00:00.708 --> 1:00:02.458
- No chimney.
We're going through the front door.

1:00:02.458 --> 1:00:03.458
Will you put your beard on?

1:00:03.458 --> 1:00:04.875
- Is there a chimney
that goes through the door?

1:00:04.875 --> 1:00:06.708
- That doesn't make any sense.
We have to go.

1:00:06.708 --> 1:00:07.542
- Okay. Let's go!

1:00:08.958 --> 1:00:10.292
HAGS:
Okay, look here, Tiny Tim.

1:00:10.292 --> 1:00:13.333
Let's be reasonable. I made a fair trade!
- No!

1:00:13.333 --> 1:00:15.208
GRETA:
[singing] Look who I found!

1:00:15.208 --> 1:00:16.375
- Ho-ho-ho!

1:00:16.375 --> 1:00:17.375
- Merry Christmas!

1:00:17.375 --> 1:00:19.167
- That fucker took my white elephant!

1:00:19.167 --> 1:00:21.250
- Sammy, language! Get back here!

1:00:21.250 --> 1:00:23.417
Security!
- No need. I'm leaving.

1:00:23.417 --> 1:00:24.667
I'm leaving!

1:00:25.375 --> 1:00:26.375
[thuds]

1:00:27.000 --> 1:00:28.917
- Shit. Shit. Shit.

1:00:28.917 --> 1:00:31.792
- Oops.
- God damn it. Get an ice pack!

1:00:31.792 --> 1:00:32.792
Jesus!

1:00:34.000 --> 1:00:36.083
♪ eerie music playing ♪

1:00:36.083 --> 1:00:39.875
KIMMI:
You know, I think I'm leaving the K hole.

1:00:39.875 --> 1:00:41.583
SARAH:
Yeah, I think maybe I feel normal now.

1:00:41.583 --> 1:00:43.625
We're gonna find that fucker in here.

1:00:44.625 --> 1:00:47.333
[in Sarah's voice] Wait, what the fuck?

1:00:47.333 --> 1:00:48.750
- [in Kimmi's voice] What is happening?

1:00:48.750 --> 1:00:50.667
- [in Sarah's voice]
I think we Freaky Friday'd.

1:00:51.542 --> 1:00:52.792
- [in Kimmi's voice] No!

1:00:54.042 --> 1:00:55.833
I don't want your voice!

1:00:55.833 --> 1:00:58.625
- [in Sarah's voice] What? Why?
What's wrong with my voice?

1:00:58.625 --> 1:01:00.125
- [in Kimmi's voice, mocking]
What's wrong with my voice?

1:01:00.125 --> 1:01:01.458
That's me doing you as you.

1:01:01.458 --> 1:01:02.875
It's not very pleasant.

1:01:02.875 --> 1:01:05.333
[voice distorts and echoes]

1:01:07.000 --> 1:01:10.000
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

1:01:12.708 --> 1:01:15.292
[owl hooting]

1:01:16.333 --> 1:01:19.042
[bird cawing]

1:01:21.500 --> 1:01:23.875
- [echoing] Yahtzee!

1:01:23.875 --> 1:01:29.542
- [echoing] Alexa... Alexa...
turn the Titilator to a 20.

1:01:29.542 --> 1:01:32.458
[cackles]

1:01:35.083 --> 1:01:36.208
- [in normal voice] Kimmi!

1:01:36.875 --> 1:01:37.875
- Excuse me!

1:01:37.875 --> 1:01:39.833
- That's the girl
that Hags is cheating on me with.

1:01:39.833 --> 1:01:41.667
- This guy got knocked out.
Can you help me?

1:01:41.667 --> 1:01:44.333
- Yeah, I'll help you.
Help you die, bitch.

1:01:44.333 --> 1:01:46.750
- What? I don't have time for this.

1:01:46.750 --> 1:01:48.458
KIMMI:
Oh, my God. Abort! She's gonna--

1:01:48.458 --> 1:01:51.500
[girls scream]
[fire extinguisher hissing]

1:01:52.958 --> 1:01:56.333
- Oh, man, I'm doing this.
I'm really doing this.

1:01:56.333 --> 1:01:59.000
♪ soft music playing ♪

1:01:59.000 --> 1:02:02.750
- Well, I'm not gonna lie,
I don't really remember the plan.

1:02:03.375 --> 1:02:07.833
But I think
you're making the-- the right choice.

1:02:07.833 --> 1:02:08.833
- Yeah.

1:02:08.833 --> 1:02:11.375
Once I drop
my baby self over for adoption,

1:02:11.375 --> 1:02:13.083
everyone's life will be much, much better.

1:02:13.083 --> 1:02:14.875
Nature versus nurture. [chuckles]

1:02:14.875 --> 1:02:17.583
Yeah, um, but before I do that,

1:02:17.583 --> 1:02:18.917
do you have any more
of that golden powder?

1:02:18.917 --> 1:02:21.958
- No! You smoked it all,
you greedy bastard.

1:02:21.958 --> 1:02:23.292
- Oh, shit.

1:02:23.292 --> 1:02:25.208
[sirens wailing]
HAGS: Andrew?

1:02:25.875 --> 1:02:27.208
- I think it's starting to wear off.

1:02:27.792 --> 1:02:29.000
- That's not good.

1:02:29.000 --> 1:02:31.000
HAGS: Andrew?
- Who said that?

1:02:31.000 --> 1:02:32.000
HAGS:
Andrew?

1:02:32.500 --> 1:02:33.917
- Baby didn't say it.

1:02:33.917 --> 1:02:36.250
HAGS: Andrew?
- Hags?

1:02:36.750 --> 1:02:39.708
- Bags? Who's Bags?
- Hags.

1:02:40.375 --> 1:02:42.500
HAGS: Andrew?
- Hags?

1:02:42.500 --> 1:02:44.167
- Andrew,
what the fuck happened to your face?

1:02:44.167 --> 1:02:46.083
And where'd you get that baby?

1:02:46.083 --> 1:02:47.333
- Where'd you get that baby?

1:02:47.333 --> 1:02:50.250
- You stole a baby?
Oh, you're going to prison.

1:02:50.250 --> 1:02:52.167
I can't help you. Goodbye.

1:02:52.167 --> 1:02:53.500
- Who is that?

1:02:54.500 --> 1:02:55.750
- Thank God!

1:02:55.750 --> 1:02:58.458
This guy tried
to steal presents from orphans.

1:02:58.458 --> 1:03:01.708
And then, this guy with the long hair
stole a baby, I think.

1:03:01.708 --> 1:03:03.583
- Stole a baby?
- I just--

1:03:03.583 --> 1:03:05.417
- We're here
because there's an escaped convict

1:03:05.417 --> 1:03:07.000
somewhere in this place dressed as Santa.

1:03:07.000 --> 1:03:09.875
- Oh, my God! He's upstairs!

1:03:09.875 --> 1:03:11.333
- Take care of these guys.

1:03:11.333 --> 1:03:14.042
- Do... not... move.

1:03:15.917 --> 1:03:16.917
Whose baby is that?

1:03:16.917 --> 1:03:18.458
- I can explain easily.

1:03:18.458 --> 1:03:19.917
- He can explain.
- Yeah.

1:03:19.917 --> 1:03:22.000
- I'm waitin'.
- It's actually pretty simple.

1:03:22.000 --> 1:03:24.167
I went back in time
thanks to this guy named Angel

1:03:24.167 --> 1:03:26.875
that I met under a bridge
after I got attacked by the Christmas Owl.

1:03:26.875 --> 1:03:29.750
He showed me that my family's better off
without me in their lives.

1:03:29.750 --> 1:03:31.458
So I went to the hospital,
stole my baby self,

1:03:31.458 --> 1:03:32.708
and now I'm here
to set him up for adoption

1:03:32.708 --> 1:03:35.042
so that, hopefully, I get a better life!

1:03:36.458 --> 1:03:37.917
- Fuckin' Binge.

1:03:37.917 --> 1:03:41.208
Why, oh, why did they have
to put The Binge on Christmas?

1:03:41.208 --> 1:03:42.208
- I know!

1:03:42.208 --> 1:03:43.625
OFFICER:
What the hell is wrong with you?

1:03:43.625 --> 1:03:45.333
You sucked it down pipe, didn't you?

1:03:46.208 --> 1:03:49.750
Give me this. Stealing from the kids!
You should be ashamed of yourself.

1:03:50.250 --> 1:03:54.125
- I want the elves to build
the perfect family... for all of us.

1:03:54.125 --> 1:03:57.042
And I'm sorry
I called that guy a fucker before.

1:03:57.625 --> 1:03:59.250
I hope you don't hold it against me.

1:03:59.250 --> 1:04:03.125
- [laughs] Sammy,
Santa doesn't hold grudges.

1:04:03.125 --> 1:04:05.208
But that is a bad word,
and you shouldn't say it.

1:04:05.208 --> 1:04:06.667
And it's hard not to.

1:04:06.667 --> 1:04:09.542
Sometimes even Santa says it.

1:04:09.542 --> 1:04:11.167
You know, the reindeer will bite me,

1:04:11.167 --> 1:04:13.958
and I want to be like, "Whoa, you fucker!"

1:04:14.833 --> 1:04:16.083
But I don't.

1:04:16.083 --> 1:04:20.042
And I wish you and all the children
to find the perfect home.

1:04:20.042 --> 1:04:24.417
And you can
if you just have faith, all right?

1:04:24.417 --> 1:04:29.750
And right now, I'm gonna need all of you
to help save Christmas this year.

1:04:30.250 --> 1:04:31.875
We need to go to a place

1:04:31.875 --> 1:04:35.208
that is the heart
and the soul of Christmas.

1:04:35.208 --> 1:04:38.500
Let's go to Winter Wonderland!

1:04:38.500 --> 1:04:41.250
[kids cheering]
- Yes! All right, let's go!

1:04:41.250 --> 1:04:42.625
- He's trying to steal the kids!

1:04:42.625 --> 1:04:44.458
- They're gonna kill Santa!
OFFICER: That's not Santa.

1:04:44.458 --> 1:04:46.542
It's just a guy dressed up.

1:04:47.542 --> 1:04:48.667
Tell the orphans.

1:04:50.458 --> 1:04:54.125
- Well, if I'm not Santa,
then how do I remember this?

1:04:55.000 --> 1:04:57.375
Christmas 2006,

1:04:57.375 --> 1:05:01.417
I went down your chimney,
and I left an iPod mini, a Nerf football,

1:05:01.417 --> 1:05:06.667
and a lava lamp from Spencer's Gifts,
just like you wanted.

1:05:06.667 --> 1:05:11.083
You left me a glass of almond milk
with an oatmeal cookie,

1:05:11.083 --> 1:05:15.208
which I ate half of just to let you know
that I'd been there.

1:05:15.875 --> 1:05:19.500
Your house was the epitome of Americana,

1:05:19.500 --> 1:05:23.667
white picket fence
and two golden retrievers.

1:05:23.667 --> 1:05:24.667
- Wow.

1:05:25.583 --> 1:05:29.625
♪ rousing music playing ♪

1:05:32.458 --> 1:05:34.833
- I was raised in a shit-hole apartment
on 8th Avenue.

1:05:36.125 --> 1:05:37.250
No pets.

1:05:37.250 --> 1:05:38.625
And I'm Jewish.

1:05:39.417 --> 1:05:40.625
[handcuffs clink]

1:05:43.500 --> 1:05:45.625
- We're all Jewish.
- No, we're not.

1:05:45.625 --> 1:05:48.125
- It was... a firehouse.

1:05:48.125 --> 1:05:50.125
That's where you lived, a firehouse.
- All right, let's go.

1:05:50.125 --> 1:05:51.958
- You had 14 cats.

1:05:51.958 --> 1:05:53.292
- No pets. I told you.

1:05:53.292 --> 1:05:54.417
He's not Santa.

1:05:54.417 --> 1:05:55.875
- He's made out of wood!

1:05:55.875 --> 1:05:57.500
- Flesh and bones.
You're under arrest. Let's go.

1:05:57.500 --> 1:05:59.208
[muffled whispering]

1:05:59.208 --> 1:06:00.250
- It's okay.

1:06:00.250 --> 1:06:03.917
♪ whimsical music playing ♪

1:06:10.917 --> 1:06:12.500
- Whoa, I know you!

1:06:13.000 --> 1:06:14.500
You're my future wife!

1:06:15.167 --> 1:06:16.875
[girls scream]

1:06:18.417 --> 1:06:19.417
- [gasps] Oh!

1:06:19.417 --> 1:06:21.667
[baby whimpering]

1:06:23.458 --> 1:06:27.417
- Hi. Wondering if you had a baby stolen
from your hospital tonight?

1:06:28.250 --> 1:06:29.750
Yeah. I know.

1:06:29.750 --> 1:06:32.083
I don't know why they would
make The Binge on Christmas either.

1:06:32.583 --> 1:06:34.083
- I need that fucking owl.

1:06:34.083 --> 1:06:37.208
- Jesus Christ, Kimmi.
Give it up already. Who cares?

1:06:38.167 --> 1:06:40.292
- I care. I care, Sarah.

1:06:40.292 --> 1:06:42.667
I've been doing everything
that you care about all night!

1:06:42.667 --> 1:06:45.833
I'm literally at the orphanage
because you needed to find Hags.

1:06:45.833 --> 1:06:48.542
- Who?
- Sarah, it's okay to be sad.

1:06:48.542 --> 1:06:52.000
You guys dated for a long time.
Just let it out.

1:06:52.000 --> 1:06:55.417
- Kimmi, can you just give up the act
for like 30 seconds?

1:06:56.000 --> 1:06:57.875
You've been saying shit
like you're my therapist,

1:06:57.875 --> 1:06:59.875
and I've been tolerating it all night.

1:06:59.875 --> 1:07:01.875
- You're not a walk in the park either.

1:07:01.875 --> 1:07:04.167
I mean, sometimes
I literally think you're, like, acting up

1:07:04.167 --> 1:07:05.500
'cause you're jealous or something.

1:07:06.333 --> 1:07:07.917
- I'm jealous of you?

1:07:07.917 --> 1:07:10.333
- You're jealous of me
because I have a life

1:07:10.333 --> 1:07:13.000
and I have new things to do
and new responsibilities,

1:07:13.000 --> 1:07:15.458
and you're still out there
calling yourself a prom queen.

1:07:17.083 --> 1:07:18.292
- You do you, Kimmi.

1:07:18.292 --> 1:07:21.667
And for your information,
I graduated eighth in my class

1:07:21.667 --> 1:07:23.542
in online cosmetology school,

1:07:23.542 --> 1:07:28.000
which you would know if you cared about
talking about anyone other than yourself.

1:07:29.375 --> 1:07:34.250
Good luck finding your owl
and in all your future endeavors.

1:07:35.250 --> 1:07:36.292
- Right!

1:07:36.292 --> 1:07:39.583
POMPANO MIKE: They got 'em all. Dang it!
DELRAY DONNA: Oh, man! Scooped 'em.

1:07:39.583 --> 1:07:41.583
POMPANO MIKE: There's only one thing
we can do at this point,

1:07:41.583 --> 1:07:43.500
good old-fashioned heist.

1:07:43.500 --> 1:07:45.125
Ocean's Eleven style.

1:07:45.125 --> 1:07:47.833
- But there's only us. Oceans Two?

1:07:47.833 --> 1:07:48.750
POMPANO MIKE:
Hear me out here.

1:07:48.750 --> 1:07:50.833
Remember that barbershop quartet
I was in?

1:07:50.833 --> 1:07:52.458
- We Cut Hair and Sing?
POMPANO MIKE: No, no.

1:07:52.458 --> 1:07:54.083
That was the first one.
The one after that.

1:07:54.083 --> 1:07:56.042
- Big Old Pump
and the Tiny, Tiny Pom Poms?

1:07:56.042 --> 1:07:57.917
- Nope. You jumped two.
The one right in the middle.

1:07:57.917 --> 1:07:59.750
- Yellow Brick Road Scholars?

1:07:59.750 --> 1:08:01.292
- No, no, that was the last one.
The middle one.

1:08:01.292 --> 1:08:04.125
- Oh! We Sing Songs?
- Yes. We Sing Songs.

1:08:04.125 --> 1:08:07.042
So that's three more guys.
That gets us to Ocean's Five.

1:08:07.042 --> 1:08:11.375
But wait, I heard Geppetto
swore off quartetting forever

1:08:11.375 --> 1:08:12.792
for religious reasons.

1:08:12.792 --> 1:08:15.292
Says that baritone is the devil's pitch.

1:08:15.292 --> 1:08:16.583
DELRAY DONNA: That's too bad.
- I know.

1:08:16.583 --> 1:08:18.458
- He was quite a talent.
- He really was.

1:08:18.458 --> 1:08:21.708
- Okay, so without Geppetto, Ocean's Four?

1:08:21.708 --> 1:08:23.208
- Darn it. You know, you're right.

1:08:23.208 --> 1:08:25.417
Any way you slice it,
we're never gonna get to Eleven.

1:08:25.417 --> 1:08:26.792
- No.
[Pompano Mike sighs]

1:08:26.792 --> 1:08:28.500
POMPANO MIKE: Well, I guess
we're gonna have to do this one solo.

1:08:28.500 --> 1:08:30.542
And by solo, I mean me and you.

1:08:32.333 --> 1:08:33.625
But when we work together,

1:08:34.417 --> 1:08:35.750
you and me,

1:08:35.750 --> 1:08:38.625
we can get through anything
life throws at us!

1:08:38.625 --> 1:08:39.792
Ain't that right, baby?

1:08:40.625 --> 1:08:43.125
[Delray Donna snoring]

1:08:43.125 --> 1:08:45.000
- You grew up on 8th Avenue.

1:08:45.000 --> 1:08:47.667
It was a small apartment. No pets.

1:08:47.667 --> 1:08:49.458
- Yeah, I told you all that stuff
at the orphanage.

1:08:50.042 --> 1:08:51.458
- Yeah, I know. I'd already known that.

1:08:51.458 --> 1:08:52.792
I was just having fun with you.

1:08:53.542 --> 1:08:54.750
- Sure.

1:08:54.750 --> 1:08:56.917
- I never delivered presents to you
'cause you were Jewish,

1:08:56.917 --> 1:08:58.625
but your neighbors, Barbara and Henry,

1:08:58.625 --> 1:09:00.250
they had a daughter named Patty,

1:09:00.250 --> 1:09:01.333
and the family owned a bakery,

1:09:01.333 --> 1:09:02.917
and they would leave me
really good cookies.

1:09:02.917 --> 1:09:04.417
Yeah, they were a really nice family.

1:09:05.250 --> 1:09:06.792
We'll be outta here, guys. Don't worry.

1:09:06.792 --> 1:09:08.167
- [softly]
I didn't tell him any of those things.

1:09:08.167 --> 1:09:11.542
- If this motherfucker is really Santa,
that's on you.

1:09:12.792 --> 1:09:13.792
Love you, Santa.

1:09:14.875 --> 1:09:17.000
- So you're just not gonna talk to me now?

1:09:17.000 --> 1:09:19.208
- You hung up on me, man.
- I called you back.

1:09:19.208 --> 1:09:20.375
- You did?
- Yes!

1:09:20.375 --> 1:09:24.208
- Oh, okay,
'cause I was in a dark place, okay?

1:09:25.125 --> 1:09:28.375
I felt like my family
would be better off without me,

1:09:28.375 --> 1:09:30.292
and I met this guy Angel

1:09:30.292 --> 1:09:33.625
who actually showed me
what my family'd be like without me,

1:09:35.500 --> 1:09:36.708
and, well, I was right.

1:09:38.250 --> 1:09:40.542
- No, Andrew, you were wrong.

1:09:41.125 --> 1:09:42.625
Because I'm your family.

1:09:42.625 --> 1:09:44.000
If I'd have known you were in trouble,

1:09:44.000 --> 1:09:46.250
I would've dropped everything I was doing
to be by your side.

1:09:48.125 --> 1:09:49.417
There's always room for family.

1:09:51.875 --> 1:09:53.042
- Dominic Toretto.

1:09:54.833 --> 1:09:55.833
Fast Five.

1:10:01.625 --> 1:10:02.958
- All right, you each get a phone call.

1:10:03.375 --> 1:10:05.125
Jailhouse Jesus, you're up first.

1:10:05.125 --> 1:10:06.167
- Pass.

1:10:06.167 --> 1:10:08.375
- You don't have
anyone to call on Christmas?

1:10:08.375 --> 1:10:11.458
- Well, anyone I'd call
is in this jail cell with me right now.

1:10:12.542 --> 1:10:14.542
- Wow. That's sad.

1:10:15.375 --> 1:10:16.542
Pathetic, actually.

1:10:17.458 --> 1:10:20.458
I have like 10 people
off the top of my head I could call,

1:10:20.458 --> 1:10:21.625
20 probably.

1:10:22.250 --> 1:10:24.417
Kayla, you got people
you could call, right?

1:10:24.417 --> 1:10:25.542
- Every damn day.

1:10:25.542 --> 1:10:27.083
- Every day,
she has friends she could call.

1:10:27.083 --> 1:10:29.167
What about you?
You got someone you wanna call?

1:10:29.167 --> 1:10:30.583
- Yeah, you should call Sarah.

1:10:31.583 --> 1:10:33.667
- Uh... yeah.

1:10:34.583 --> 1:10:36.458
Yeah, I'll-- I'll take my call.

1:10:36.458 --> 1:10:38.333
- Of course, he's gonna make a call.
Everyone should.

1:10:38.333 --> 1:10:40.042
KAYLE: What a loser.
- Find friends.

1:10:40.042 --> 1:10:42.958
KAYLA: I have no respect for people
who have no long-term relationships.

1:10:44.083 --> 1:10:45.792
DELRAY DONNA:
Sure no one will notice us here?

1:10:45.792 --> 1:10:47.042
POMPANO MIKE:
There's no way they could.

1:10:47.042 --> 1:10:48.208
Here's the plan.

1:10:48.208 --> 1:10:50.625
I'm gonna be responsible
for sneaking the guys out.

1:10:50.625 --> 1:10:53.708
That means all you have to do
is hack into the mainframe

1:10:53.708 --> 1:10:56.375
and shut down the cameras,
the security system,

1:10:56.375 --> 1:10:58.000
and the locking mechanism to the cell.

1:10:58.000 --> 1:11:01.000
From there, you're gonna
shadow ban yourself on the dark web.

1:11:01.000 --> 1:11:03.125
- You're gonna be completely incognito.
- All right.

1:11:03.125 --> 1:11:04.208
- Then you're gonna go in,

1:11:04.208 --> 1:11:08.333
reroute all the calls
in the local area 40 miles east,

1:11:08.333 --> 1:11:10.083
sending the squad cars away.

1:11:10.083 --> 1:11:13.125
- Mainframe.
- Yeah. Squad cars away.

1:11:14.000 --> 1:11:15.375
- Wait, you want me to do this?

1:11:15.375 --> 1:11:19.083
- Yeah, we don't have a full eleven,
so I allocated all the tech stuff to you.

1:11:19.083 --> 1:11:22.042
- Well, I don't know how
to do any of the stuff you just said.

1:11:22.042 --> 1:11:24.458
- Not even a simple vector decoy or...

1:11:24.458 --> 1:11:26.625
- Just give me one sec.
- Yep.

1:11:30.000 --> 1:11:33.000
♪ soft ethereal music playing ♪

1:11:33.875 --> 1:11:35.333
- I got it.
- Nice.

1:11:35.333 --> 1:11:38.750
- I saw this episode of Cops once
where this guy did a shit ton of PCP.

1:11:39.250 --> 1:11:41.875
He got hit by a monster truck,
didn't feel a thing!

1:11:41.875 --> 1:11:43.792
You do a gentleman's dose,

1:11:43.792 --> 1:11:45.875
get in there,
distract the shit out of 'em.

1:11:45.875 --> 1:11:47.583
You'll be virtually invincible.

1:11:47.583 --> 1:11:49.708
I'll get in and get the keys to the cell.

1:11:52.833 --> 1:11:54.542
- We're gonna make great parents one day.

1:11:54.542 --> 1:11:55.750
- I love you.
- Love you too.

1:11:55.750 --> 1:11:56.750
- Okay.

1:11:58.708 --> 1:12:00.208
- So just a gentleman's amount.

1:12:03.750 --> 1:12:05.208
[snorts sharply]

1:12:05.208 --> 1:12:06.750
♪ dark rumbling music playing ♪

1:12:06.750 --> 1:12:09.375
[howling]

1:12:09.375 --> 1:12:10.375
[thunder cracks]

1:12:10.958 --> 1:12:13.375
- Hi, I am...

1:12:15.833 --> 1:12:16.833
Pompano Mike,

1:12:17.333 --> 1:12:21.000
and I just had a question about
some people that you took in tonight.

1:12:21.000 --> 1:12:25.208
- Are you a relative
or legal guardian, Mike?

1:12:25.208 --> 1:12:28.208
- Uhhhh...

1:12:31.292 --> 1:12:33.708
Look. Look at this.

1:12:33.708 --> 1:12:36.875
[Pompano Mike screaming]

1:12:38.458 --> 1:12:41.458
Oh, my God! Are you seeing this?

1:12:41.458 --> 1:12:44.667
- Hey, sir. I'm gonna need you to stop it.

1:12:44.667 --> 1:12:47.625
- Oh, man! What's happening?
[Pompano Mike continues screaming]

1:12:48.917 --> 1:12:51.042
Who is this guy?
POMPANO MIKE: I think it's working.

1:12:51.542 --> 1:12:54.292
[Pompano Mike screaming]
[glass shatters]

1:12:55.917 --> 1:12:57.292
Yeah, yeah, okay, we're good.

1:12:57.292 --> 1:13:00.292
♪ upbeat music playing ♪

1:13:06.333 --> 1:13:07.958
- Another Merry Christmas call.

1:13:07.958 --> 1:13:09.458
- You have too many friends.

1:13:09.458 --> 1:13:11.708
[Pompano Mike screaming in distance]

1:13:17.042 --> 1:13:18.208
[ornaments clattering]

1:13:19.583 --> 1:13:21.375
- Pompano Mike,
what the hell are you doing here?

1:13:21.375 --> 1:13:23.667
- Should we be concerned about this?
POMPANO MIKE: To rescue you guys!

1:13:23.667 --> 1:13:24.875
- No. Not at all.

1:13:24.875 --> 1:13:26.625
[Pompano Mike screaming]

1:13:30.542 --> 1:13:33.667
Ah! Cops! Take that!
- All right.

1:13:34.833 --> 1:13:39.083
- Terminator 2.
Terminator 2. Terminator 2!

1:13:39.083 --> 1:13:41.167
Come on, Terminator 2.

1:13:41.167 --> 1:13:45.375
Ah, what the fuck?
They-- They put away Santa? That's it!

1:13:45.375 --> 1:13:47.167
- Ooh.
- Let me in there, pal.

1:13:47.167 --> 1:13:48.167
- Okay, okay.

1:13:48.167 --> 1:13:49.292
- Let me in there right now.

1:13:49.292 --> 1:13:51.667
HAGS: Those aren't real guns, guys.
He's not armed.

1:13:52.667 --> 1:13:54.250
- I am armed.

1:13:54.250 --> 1:13:56.750
[laughs] You don't wanna know
what these bullets feel like.

1:13:56.750 --> 1:13:59.250
Hey, Santa, what's up?
- Hi.

1:13:59.250 --> 1:14:01.292
- This is what you get
when you fuck with Santa!

1:14:02.333 --> 1:14:04.333
Now close it.
OFFICER: You asked for this.

1:14:04.333 --> 1:14:06.792
- Close it up! That's good.

1:14:06.792 --> 1:14:10.083
That's a good guy. That's a good guy.

1:14:10.083 --> 1:14:11.292
- There you go, partner.

1:14:11.292 --> 1:14:13.917
POMPANO MIKE: All right, guys.
It's gonna take all of us this time.

1:14:13.917 --> 1:14:14.917
Let's go!

1:14:14.917 --> 1:14:16.792
[screams] Come on!

1:14:16.792 --> 1:14:19.917
[Andrew and Pompano Mike
screaming "Terminator 2"]

1:14:19.917 --> 1:14:22.125
- Woo!

1:14:32.125 --> 1:14:35.125
♪ eerie music playing ♪

1:14:36.417 --> 1:14:39.417
♪ "Ode to Joy" playing ♪

1:14:53.708 --> 1:14:54.750
- Thank you, Diane.

1:14:54.750 --> 1:14:57.167
We are here live at Winter Wonderland

1:14:57.167 --> 1:15:00.792
where it appears that the Bingers
are staging a mutiny.

1:15:00.792 --> 1:15:03.167
Mayor Spengler
has completely lost control.

1:15:03.167 --> 1:15:08.208
Her request to keep this event Binge free
has only made people want to binge more.

1:15:08.208 --> 1:15:09.375
It's funny how that works.

1:15:09.375 --> 1:15:12.000
I pulled a cupcake off one of the trays
when I entered in here,

1:15:12.000 --> 1:15:15.417
and now people's faces are starting
to melt and turn neon.

1:15:15.417 --> 1:15:17.083
I guess it was laced with something.

1:15:17.083 --> 1:15:19.292
Par for the course for The Binge,
I suppose.

1:15:19.292 --> 1:15:22.625
And I guess that's par for the course
for The Binge, I suppose.

1:15:22.625 --> 1:15:25.458
I'm sorry. Did I just say that,
or did I think that?

1:15:25.458 --> 1:15:26.833
I don't know.

1:15:26.833 --> 1:15:30.208
But I do know it's par for the course
for The Binge.

1:15:30.208 --> 1:15:33.208
[crowd chanting "Binge!"]

1:15:35.917 --> 1:15:37.917
[tree thuds]
[crowd gasps]

1:15:39.250 --> 1:15:41.250
[crowd cheering]

1:15:41.250 --> 1:15:42.792
- Fuckin' Binge.

1:15:42.792 --> 1:15:45.250
- Long live The Binge!

1:15:45.250 --> 1:15:46.667
♪ bright cheery music playing ♪

1:15:46.667 --> 1:15:47.958
KAYLA:
Now this is Christmas.

1:15:49.208 --> 1:15:50.292
OFFICER:
Got another one.

1:15:50.292 --> 1:15:52.208
He was standing
in someone's living room,

1:15:52.208 --> 1:15:54.625
pretending to be a ghost
and eating their food.

1:15:54.625 --> 1:15:56.250
- I love chicken wings.

1:15:56.250 --> 1:15:59.542
Oh, my mother's golden brown--
- Angel?

1:15:59.542 --> 1:16:00.583
ANGEL:
Anderooney!

1:16:00.583 --> 1:16:04.875
Look what I got
from the orphanage! [giggles]

1:16:05.458 --> 1:16:06.708
Merry Bingemas!

1:16:06.708 --> 1:16:09.250
- Oh, fuck it.
It's already the worst Christmas ever.

1:16:09.958 --> 1:16:10.958
Let's go.

1:16:10.958 --> 1:16:12.833
♪ bright harp music playing ♪

1:16:12.833 --> 1:16:14.042
ANGEL:
Binge!

1:16:16.125 --> 1:16:19.125
- ♪ It's the worst Christmas ever ♪

1:16:19.125 --> 1:16:22.042
- ♪ There's no love for me this year ♪

1:16:22.042 --> 1:16:25.167
- ♪ No, we won't be together ♪

1:16:25.167 --> 1:16:27.958
