1:16:27.958 --> 1:16:31.125
♪ No ho-ho-hos, no mistletoes ♪

1:16:31.125 --> 1:16:34.125
♪ No angels getting wings ♪

1:16:34.125 --> 1:16:36.375
♪ It's the worst Christmas ever ♪

1:16:36.375 --> 1:16:37.375
[set thuds]

1:16:37.375 --> 1:16:40.833
♪ 'Cause The Binge has gone
and ruined everything ♪

1:16:40.833 --> 1:16:41.917
[snorting]

1:16:41.917 --> 1:16:43.583
- ♪ Well, I was gonna propose ♪

1:16:43.583 --> 1:16:45.875
♪ Now I'm totally hosed
and I'm haunted by this ring ♪

1:16:45.875 --> 1:16:48.583
- ♪ And now I'm all alone
sitting on my throne ♪

1:16:48.583 --> 1:16:52.292
♪ Still looking for my homecoming king ♪

1:16:52.292 --> 1:16:53.833
- ♪ I saw the future, I saw the past ♪

1:16:53.833 --> 1:16:56.208
♪ I need The Binge to end at last ♪

1:16:56.208 --> 1:16:58.417
- ♪ Yeah, I'm on the prowl
for the stupid owl ♪

1:16:58.417 --> 1:17:00.250
♪ And Kimberly, seriously ♪

1:17:00.250 --> 1:17:01.083
[owl screeches]

1:17:01.083 --> 1:17:05.250
♪ Maybe I'm growing up way too fast ♪

1:17:05.250 --> 1:17:08.333
- ♪ It's the worst Christmas ever ♪

1:17:08.333 --> 1:17:12.167
- ♪ Who thought it was smart for The Binge
to start on this jolly holiday? ♪

1:17:12.167 --> 1:17:14.292
♪ I just wanted to see my family ♪

1:17:14.292 --> 1:17:18.375
♪ But now I better
head back up north on my sleigh ♪

1:17:18.375 --> 1:17:20.375
- ♪ I pimped my ride, my girl by my side ♪

1:17:20.375 --> 1:17:22.000
♪ I thought I was in heaven ♪

1:17:22.000 --> 1:17:24.583
♪ But The Binge made me realize ♪

1:17:24.583 --> 1:17:29.667
♪ I'll never have my own Ocean's Eleven ♪

1:17:29.667 --> 1:17:31.250
- ♪ Well, you see, way back in the day ♪

1:17:31.250 --> 1:17:32.417
♪ I killed a guy in LA ♪

1:17:32.417 --> 1:17:34.458
♪ And this other bro
living in San Antonio ♪

1:17:34.458 --> 1:17:36.417
♪ Had a bit of a spree in Tallahassee ♪

1:17:36.417 --> 1:17:38.333
♪ Gotta get this off of my chest ♪

1:17:38.333 --> 1:17:41.292
♪ 'Cause there never was an arrest ♪

1:17:41.292 --> 1:17:42.958
- ♪ It's the worst Christmas-- ♪

1:17:42.958 --> 1:17:44.125
- Wait, wait, wait, wait, hold on.

1:17:44.125 --> 1:17:45.333
Hold on. That wasn't all.

1:17:45.333 --> 1:17:46.583
I killed a guy in St. Paul

1:17:46.583 --> 1:17:49.958
and a few others
at a mall in Niagara Falls. Oh, and--

1:17:49.958 --> 1:17:53.250
- Angel, I don't think you should
be incriminating yourself like this.

1:17:53.250 --> 1:17:56.125
- Oh, I thought
this song was a safe space.

1:17:56.125 --> 1:17:57.958
I was... kidding?

1:17:59.458 --> 1:18:02.625
- ♪ It's the worst Christmas ever ♪

1:18:02.625 --> 1:18:05.542
♪ There's no love for me this year ♪

1:18:05.542 --> 1:18:08.667
♪ No, we won't be together ♪

1:18:08.667 --> 1:18:11.750
♪ There's no bailing me outta here ♪

1:18:11.750 --> 1:18:17.417
♪ No ho-ho-hos, no mistletoes,
no angels getting wings ♪

1:18:17.917 --> 1:18:20.417
[all singing off-key]
♪ It's the worst Christmas ever ♪

1:18:20.417 --> 1:18:26.417
♪ And The Binge has gone
and ruined everything ♪

1:18:28.667 --> 1:18:29.917
- Good God!

1:18:29.917 --> 1:18:31.250
- Fellas, take it from the top.

1:18:31.250 --> 1:18:33.125
- No, no, no. No. Good news, folks.

1:18:33.125 --> 1:18:35.125
We don't normally have
our holding tank full

1:18:35.125 --> 1:18:36.708
of a bunch of singing people
on Christmas Eve.

1:18:37.208 --> 1:18:39.292
KAYLA: And if this many people
are trying to bail you out,

1:18:39.292 --> 1:18:41.333
then you must be something pretty special.

1:18:41.333 --> 1:18:42.667
Come on in, family.

1:18:43.167 --> 1:18:46.708
- Ah! [laughs]
- Shit. Mom?

1:18:46.708 --> 1:18:48.958
- Which one do you
messed with my kid, huh? Which one?

1:18:48.958 --> 1:18:50.292
[Rigo speaking Spanish]

1:18:50.292 --> 1:18:51.208
- Dads?

1:18:51.208 --> 1:18:53.833
- Your boy Hags called us.
Been looking for you all night, man!

1:18:53.833 --> 1:18:55.958
- Wait, you have?
- Yeah.

1:18:56.375 --> 1:18:58.208
- You used your one call for me, Hags?

1:18:58.208 --> 1:19:00.958
- Yeah, man, of course!
What would Diesel do?

1:19:00.958 --> 1:19:01.958
- Wow.

1:19:01.958 --> 1:19:04.500
DEIDRE:
You're the spice of our family, Andrew.

1:19:04.917 --> 1:19:06.917
You're the testicles in the tomato soup.

1:19:07.333 --> 1:19:09.833
We need you, Andrew. We need you.

1:19:10.833 --> 1:19:13.000
RIGO:
I was being a selfish piece of shit.

1:19:13.000 --> 1:19:17.292
And I don't care whose sperm
Rube Goldberg'd with another sperm

1:19:17.292 --> 1:19:22.458
to fertilize an egg that ultimately led
to two vastly different twins.

1:19:23.875 --> 1:19:25.375
You'll always be a part of me.

1:19:25.875 --> 1:19:29.958
I wouldn't trade you
for all the Titcoin in the world.

1:19:29.958 --> 1:19:32.167
- [Deidre speaking Spanish]
...Titcoin.

1:19:32.167 --> 1:19:35.542
- Wow. I've never heard you
say something like that to me.

1:19:35.542 --> 1:19:36.792
That's, uh... [chuckles]

1:19:37.750 --> 1:19:38.750
That's amazing!

1:19:39.292 --> 1:19:40.542
And Dakota, you too?

1:19:40.542 --> 1:19:42.167
- I only came 'cause I like car rides.

1:19:42.583 --> 1:19:44.250
- Appreciate that. Thank you.

1:19:45.000 --> 1:19:46.917
Well, it's a Christmas miracle.

1:19:48.083 --> 1:19:49.458
I love my family.

1:19:50.333 --> 1:19:51.458
I love my family!

1:19:51.458 --> 1:19:53.333
[everyone laughs]

1:19:53.333 --> 1:19:56.167
ALL:
I love my family!

1:19:57.958 --> 1:19:59.500
- Angel, I get it now.

1:19:59.500 --> 1:20:01.208
- Have we met?
- Yes, we have met!

1:20:01.208 --> 1:20:02.208
We went through a whole--

1:20:03.250 --> 1:20:05.167
I understand what you were trying
to teach me this whole time.

1:20:05.167 --> 1:20:06.333
- You do?

1:20:06.333 --> 1:20:07.708
ANDREW:
You were trying to teach me

1:20:07.708 --> 1:20:10.917
I actually have the ability
to make my own future.

1:20:10.917 --> 1:20:12.500
- Oh, yeah. That was the lesson.

1:20:12.500 --> 1:20:14.875
Hey, right on.
ANDREW: Hey, right on!

1:20:16.000 --> 1:20:18.458
All right, guys,
what do you say, we, uh...

1:20:19.625 --> 1:20:21.667
say fuck it,
hit the Winter Wonderland, right?

1:20:21.667 --> 1:20:23.792
Reunite my mom with that weird-ass dude
that was at our dinner,

1:20:23.792 --> 1:20:25.500
and I tell Kimmi I love her
for the first time.

1:20:25.500 --> 1:20:27.875
KAYLA: Move out the way.
Enough of this sappy stuff.

1:20:27.875 --> 1:20:29.625
Please slide over if you want 'em free.

1:20:29.625 --> 1:20:30.792
Thank you, ma'am.

1:20:32.417 --> 1:20:33.833
Come on.
- All right.

1:20:34.500 --> 1:20:36.792
So, I-- It's okay if we-- Okay.

1:20:36.792 --> 1:20:39.292
DEIDRE: Come on, baby.

1:20:39.292 --> 1:20:41.208
- And you might want this.
- Thank you.

1:20:41.208 --> 1:20:43.000
- Come on, Terminator 2.
- Terminator 2.

1:20:43.000 --> 1:20:44.125
UNCLE KRIS:
This is great.

1:20:44.125 --> 1:20:46.083
- Hey, I don't know if you're Santa,

1:20:46.083 --> 1:20:49.208
but if you are,
can you look after my grandkids?

1:20:49.208 --> 1:20:50.833
- Tracy and Jamal. They're adorable.

1:20:50.833 --> 1:20:51.833
Yeah, for sure.

1:20:51.833 --> 1:20:53.917
ANGEL:
All right! Let's go feed the--

1:20:53.917 --> 1:20:56.000
- Mm-mm.
- Not you.

1:20:56.000 --> 1:20:59.000
- Hey, what happened
to all that Christmas spirit,

1:20:59.000 --> 1:21:01.208
and redemption, and cheer?

1:21:01.208 --> 1:21:03.000
OFFICER: What happened
is we ran your fingerprints,

1:21:03.000 --> 1:21:06.208
and you're wanted in 11 states
for a couple dozen murders.

1:21:06.208 --> 1:21:08.500
You're never gonna see
the light of day again.

1:21:08.500 --> 1:21:12.042
- ♪ This is the worst Christmas ever ♪

1:21:12.042 --> 1:21:13.708
- Stop singing.
No one wants to hear you sing again.

1:21:13.708 --> 1:21:14.958
- ♪ No love for me ♪

1:21:14.958 --> 1:21:16.500
KAYLA: Ah, ah, ah!
OFFICER: Back, back, back.

1:21:16.500 --> 1:21:18.167
KAYLA:
Get your ass back in there!

1:21:18.167 --> 1:21:19.542
- All right,
we gotta get to the orphanage.

1:21:19.542 --> 1:21:22.000
We gotta show the kids
what Christmas is all about.

1:21:22.625 --> 1:21:25.292
Do you have any presents or treats
or, like, candy canes or anything?

1:21:29.125 --> 1:21:30.958
- How about this for the kids?

1:21:30.958 --> 1:21:32.417
KAYLA:
Oh, hell. We'll allow it.

1:21:32.417 --> 1:21:34.792
It's a Christmas Binge. Nothing matters.

1:21:34.792 --> 1:21:36.167
- Christmas is saved!

1:21:36.167 --> 1:21:38.958
[all clap and cheer]

1:21:38.958 --> 1:21:42.000
- Love to stay for the family reunion,
but I'm gonna go propose!

1:21:42.000 --> 1:21:42.875
- Yeah!
- All right!

1:21:42.875 --> 1:21:44.333
- I'm gonna propose!
- All right!

1:21:44.333 --> 1:21:46.000
HAGS:
Okay. Love you all!

1:21:46.875 --> 1:21:51.667
[train horn honks]
[muffled chatter and laughter]

1:21:51.667 --> 1:21:54.667
♪ EDM version
of "Carol of the Bells" playing ♪

1:21:58.833 --> 1:22:01.500
MAYOR SPENGLER:
Stop! Stop it!

1:22:01.500 --> 1:22:04.083
Oh, god damn it! [indistinct shouting]

1:22:04.083 --> 1:22:07.125
Stop! No!

1:22:07.125 --> 1:22:09.208
Everyone, get out of here!
What are you doing?

1:22:09.208 --> 1:22:10.583
What's wrong with you?

1:22:11.417 --> 1:22:13.583
Oh, no, no!
Get out! Everyone get out!

1:22:13.583 --> 1:22:15.167
No, no, no!

1:22:15.167 --> 1:22:16.417
When did you do this?

1:22:16.417 --> 1:22:19.083
When did you switch out
all the music and the lights?

1:22:19.750 --> 1:22:22.583
Christmas is not about this!
It's about family!

1:22:23.417 --> 1:22:24.667
- Where's your family?

1:22:26.417 --> 1:22:27.875
- Where's my family?

1:22:29.625 --> 1:22:32.625
♪ EDM version
of "Carol of the Bells" playing ♪

1:22:48.542 --> 1:22:51.083
- Uncle Kris! What are you doing here?

1:22:51.083 --> 1:22:52.542
- Candy!

1:22:52.542 --> 1:22:53.958
- That's not candy!

1:22:53.958 --> 1:22:55.750
UNCLE KRIS:
Christmas dust!

1:22:56.250 --> 1:23:00.083
- God bless us, everyone! [snorts]

1:23:00.875 --> 1:23:04.667
This Christmas dust makes me
wanna start a small business.

1:23:05.667 --> 1:23:09.042
- It seems that the mayor's brother,
who was a felon who is dressed as Santa,

1:23:09.042 --> 1:23:11.708
is throwing drugs
to the Winter Wonderland attendees,

1:23:11.708 --> 1:23:13.125
young and old.

1:23:13.125 --> 1:23:14.500
- What did you say?
That's not my brother.

1:23:14.500 --> 1:23:16.708
That's just a fake Santa,
and they all look the same.

1:23:16.708 --> 1:23:18.125
UNCLE KRIS:
That's my sister, the mayor!

1:23:18.125 --> 1:23:19.125
KIMMI:
Mom?

1:23:19.833 --> 1:23:21.000
- Oh, my goodness!

1:23:21.000 --> 1:23:23.583
It looks like the mayor's daughter,
and she's all scratched up.

1:23:23.583 --> 1:23:25.125
MAYOR SPENGLER:
Kimmi? It's me!

1:23:26.000 --> 1:23:28.000
- The mayor has acknowledged the child,

1:23:28.000 --> 1:23:30.125
and now the child has acknowledged
the mayor.

1:23:30.125 --> 1:23:32.417
This is definitely the mayor's daughter.

1:23:32.417 --> 1:23:35.833
- [chuckles nervously] So? So? So what?

1:23:35.833 --> 1:23:38.958
- Everyone's having a great time here
except for the mayor.

1:23:38.958 --> 1:23:41.417
Church sirens are ringing
and everyone is singing...

1:23:41.417 --> 1:23:43.875
- That's not a thing!
- "Keep your hands up for Christmas."

1:23:43.875 --> 1:23:45.792
- No! God damn it!
- Keep your hands up for Christmas!

1:23:45.792 --> 1:23:47.625
[crowd chanting
"Keep your hands up for Christmas"]

1:23:49.250 --> 1:23:50.958
- Put your hands down!

1:23:50.958 --> 1:23:52.250
It's not a song!

1:23:53.542 --> 1:23:55.917
A church doesn't have a siren!

1:23:56.417 --> 1:23:57.625
- Sarah!

1:23:58.792 --> 1:23:59.833
[snowball thudding]
Sarah!

1:24:00.583 --> 1:24:01.500
Sarah!

1:24:01.500 --> 1:24:02.833
- Oh! Hags!
HAGS: What the hell?

1:24:02.833 --> 1:24:04.000
- I'm glad you came back!

1:24:04.000 --> 1:24:05.667
I've been thinking about your dinner joke!

1:24:05.667 --> 1:24:08.167
- You're a lunatic! Where's your niece?

1:24:08.167 --> 1:24:10.792
Sarah, please! Sarah!

1:24:11.750 --> 1:24:13.125
[snowball thuds]
Come on, Sarah!

1:24:13.125 --> 1:24:15.000
- It's some kind of a meta-commentary

1:24:15.000 --> 1:24:17.208
on the way
we consume meat in this country.

1:24:17.208 --> 1:24:19.875
HAGS: Did you just run to another room?
- Yeah.

1:24:20.292 --> 1:24:22.042
- It's weird, bro! Really weird!

1:24:22.042 --> 1:24:25.083
- Hags! Go away. Go home!

1:24:27.917 --> 1:24:30.583
No, don't-- don't do
the fucking card thing.

1:24:31.333 --> 1:24:34.000
You spelled my name wrong, Hags.
You put two As.

1:24:35.042 --> 1:24:36.958
How drunk were you when you wrote these?

1:24:38.667 --> 1:24:41.333
Why is that house smoking a cigarette?
- What?

1:24:42.458 --> 1:24:44.292
Okay, that's not what I meant to say.

1:24:44.292 --> 1:24:45.333
Right, this is the one though.

1:24:45.333 --> 1:24:48.875
This is what I've been wanting
to say to you the entire night, Sarah.

1:24:54.125 --> 1:24:56.583
Damn, I really was high and drunk
when I wrote these.

1:24:56.583 --> 1:24:58.000
Sarah, I just need you to listen to me.

1:24:58.000 --> 1:24:59.083
SARAH:
I don't wanna listen to you.

1:24:59.083 --> 1:25:01.958
I don't wanna see you,
and you clearly don't wanna see me.

1:25:01.958 --> 1:25:03.500
You've been acting crazy.

1:25:03.500 --> 1:25:07.042
- I'm acting crazy
because I was scared, Sarah.

1:25:07.708 --> 1:25:09.667
I thought because we were growing older

1:25:09.667 --> 1:25:12.500
that our relationship
wouldn't be able to work anymore.

1:25:12.500 --> 1:25:13.667
- Well, maybe it doesn't.

1:25:13.667 --> 1:25:15.875
- No, Sarah.
See, that's what I learned tonight.

1:25:16.375 --> 1:25:21.000
The love and the beauty of life
doesn't just die because you get older.

1:25:22.167 --> 1:25:23.167
It gets better.

1:25:24.708 --> 1:25:27.375
Because you get to share those moments
with the people you love the most.

1:25:29.042 --> 1:25:31.917
- So you really weren't having
an affair with the orphanage lady?

1:25:31.917 --> 1:25:34.500
